parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the loss of anti-lock braking, leading to increased stopping distances, loss of traction, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates
the brake light blinks or remains lit
the ABS system is not functional
the brakes lock up or pulsate
and the vehicle may experience reduced traction or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt can cause the engine to stall or seize, leading to loss of control, accidents, or engine damage.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the timing belt breaks or snaps
the engine valves and pistons collide
causing engine damage
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing belt tensioner can cause the timing belt to break or slip, leading to engine damage or loss of control.
symptoms: The timing belt breaks or slips
the engine valves and pistons collide
causing engine damage
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the engine runs poorly or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks can cause engine damage, loss of power, and accidents.
symptoms: Oil leaks from multiple locations
engine oil pressure sensor is permanently lit
the engine loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine coolant temperature sensor can cause engine damage, loss of power, and accidents.
symptoms: The engine coolant temperature sensor fails
leaking coolant into the engine control module and wire harness
causing engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Suspension Lower Control Arm Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension lower control arm can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle develops a severe vibration in the front end
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and there may be a loud grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle develops a loud noise coming from the front tie rods
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and there may be a vibration in the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle develops a loud noise coming from the steering system
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and there may be a vibration in the front end.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause loss of braking control, leading to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The brakes require extra effort and perform poorly
and there may be a warning light on the instrument panel.
